    formula: "$$\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text{For all } \\mathbf{u}, \\mathbf{v}, \\mathbf{w} \\in V \\text{ and all } c, d \\in \\mathbb{F}: \\\\\n&(1)\\ \\mathbf{u} + \\mathbf{v} \\in V \\quad (2)\\ \\mathbf{u} + \\mathbf{v} = \\mathbf{v} + \\mathbf{u} \\\\\n&(3)\\ (\\mathbf{u} + \\mathbf{v}) + \\mathbf{w} = \\mathbf{u} + (\\mathbf{v} + \\mathbf{w}) \\\\\n&(4)\\ \\exists\\, \\mathbf{0} \\in V: \\mathbf{v} + \\mathbf{0} = \\mathbf{v} \\\\\n&(5)\\ \\exists\\, -\\mathbf{v} \\in V: \\mathbf{v} + (-\\mathbf{v}) = \\mathbf{0} \\\\\n&(6)\\ c\\mathbf{v} \\in V \\quad (7)\\ c(d\\mathbf{v}) = (cd)\\mathbf{v} \\\\\n&(8)\\ c(\\mathbf{u} + \\mathbf{v}) = c\\mathbf{u} + c\\mathbf{v} \\\\\n&(9)\\ (c + d)\\mathbf{v} = c\\mathbf{v} + d\\mathbf{v} \\quad (10)\\ 1\\mathbf{v} = \\mathbf{v}\n\\end{aligned}$$",
